Six horses eat 12 bales of hay in 12 hours. At the same rate, how many hours will 36 bales of hay last 12 horses?

}

\textbf{Answer:} From the original rate, we note that 12 horses will eat 12 bales of hay in 6 hours. (Double the number of horses, half the time) Therefore, 12 horses will eat 36 bales of hay in $\boxed{18\text{ hours}}$. (Triple the amount of hay, triple the time)
